<TITLE> BCL suspends 5 DU hall activists </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 4 (bdnews24.com) Pro-government Bangladesh Chhatra League has suspended five of its activists over the clash between two rival groups of a Dhaka University residential hall early on Tuesday. General secretary of the university unit of the student organisation Sajjad Sakib Badsha confirmed bdnews24.com the disciplinary move taken on Tuesday evening. Badsha said the suspended--Farabi, Rajan and Apu of the president's group and Maidul and Parvez of the general secretary's group--were informed about the decision. At least 14 students were injured in a series of factional clashes that started at around 3:30am at Muhsin Hall over total control of the dormitory. The university unit also served show cause notices on the president Sheikh Mohammed Ali and general secretary Mohammed Mohiuddin of the hall unit . When contacted they said that they had heard about the decision over phone, but did not get the notices. Witnesses said 15 rooms of the hall were vandalised during the initial clashes that lasted for more than an hour as they traded brickbats and chased each other. Hall provost Prof Akkas Ali, university proctor KM Saiful Islam and assistant proctor Amjad Ali went to the scene along with a small contingent of police. At this point Mohiuddin's followers left the scene and Ali's men took control of the hall, according to campus sources. The injured were admitted to the university's medical centre and Dhaka Medical College Hospital near the campus. At about 9am, Mohiuddin's followers attacked one of the supporters of Ali when he was coming out of the university medical centre. Subsequently, three followers of Mohiuddin were injured when Ali's men attacked them in retaliation and the police arrested two followers of Ali  Ripon and Babu. The students supporting Ali later took out a procession and held a meeting inside the hall. PROBE COMMITTEE FORMED Authorities on Tuesday formed a three-member committee, headed by assistant residential teacher Mohammed Abu Taleb, to investigate the incident. The committee was asked to submit its report as early as possible. Senior residential teacher of the hall Abul Kalam Sarker said that the committee had already started work. BACK TO HALL Activists loyal to the general secretary entered the hall on Tuesday afternoon after mutual understanding. Mohiuddin told bdnews24.com: "The active leaders and supporters have returned hall with me in the afternoon." He also said the two groups sat at a meeting from 10am to 2:30pm at the vice-chancellor's residence at the initiative of proctor KM Saiful Islam. Hall president Moahmmed Ali told bdnews24.com there were no more problems in the hall and that everyone was staying together. However, both the groups demanded punishment of each other for the clash. bdne
